    <briefdescription>
<para>Lightweight ordered table for named values. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The table stores entries in insertion order and offers lookup by key, lookup by value, and optional uniqueness rules. It is intentionally simpler than std::map: duplicate keys and duplicate values are allowed by default, while derived classes can enable uniqueness constraints.</para>
<para>Key comparison can be case-sensitive or case-insensitive. When no matching key exists, <ref refid="class_c_named_value_table_1a556f87f5cd383b0970a87ee31a52aa88" kindref="member">get()</ref> returns the configured default value.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TValue</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Type of the stored values. The value type must be copyable and comparable with operator== for value lookups and unique-value tables. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
